Football is the number one sport in [[Ukraine]]. Ukraine has as an independent nation qualified for the [[FIFA World Cup]] once. That was in the [[2006]] tournament when they reached the quarterfinals. [[Dynamo Kiev]] and [[Shakhtyor Donetsk]] are among the big European clubs nowadays. [[Dynamo Kiev]] also was a big team in the [[Soviet]] times as they won the [[European Cup Winners Cup]] twice; namely in [[1975]] and [[1986]]. Among the famous players to come out of [[Ukraine]] it is worth mentioning [[Oleg Blokhin]] and [[Andrey Shevchenko]]. Also the legendary coach [[Valeri Lobanovski]] who led [[Dynamo Kiev]] to their [[European]] Cup victories as well as coaching th e former [[USSR]] and later on the [[Ukrainian]] national team.

